-- Ecclestone May Buy German Nuerburgring Track, Rheinpfalz Says
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2012-07-25T17:54:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-25/ecclestone-may-buy-german-nuerburgring-track-rheinpfalz-says.html
Formula One Chief Executive Officer
 Bernie Ecclestone  is interested in buying the Nuerburgring auto
track in Germany, Ludwigshafen-based  Die Rheinpfalz  reported,
citing an interview.  Ecclestone declined to comment on conditions or pricing for
a purchase, the newspaper said. The executive is not prepared to
organize a Formula One race on the track at his own expense, the
newspaper cited him as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  